    <div xml:id="PN228">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kalañcey kōvē kalañcey kōvē</l>
<l>yiruṭiṇin taṉṉa kurūuttiraṭ parūuppukai</l>
<l>yakaliru vicumpi ṉūṉṟuñ cūḷai</l>
<l>naṉantalai mūtūrk kalañcey kōvē</l>
<l>yaḷiyai nīyē yāṅkā kuvaiko</l>
<l>ṉilamvarai cūṭṭiya nīṇeṭun tāṉaip</l>
<l>pulavar pukaḻnta poyyā nallicai</l>
<l>virikatir ñāyiṟu vicumpivarn taṉṉa</l>
<l>cēṇviḷaṅku ciṟappiṟ cempiyar marukaṉ</l>
<l>koṭinuṭaṅ kiyāṉai neṭumā vaḷavaṉ</l>
<l>ṟēva rulaka meytiṉa ṉātali</l>
<l>ṉaṉṉōṟ kavikkuṅ kaṇṇakaṉ ṟāḻi</l>
<l>vaṉaital vēṭṭaṉai yāyi ṉeṉaiyatūu</l>
<l>mirunilan tikiriyāp perumalai</l>
<l>maṇṇā vaṉaita lollumō niṉakkē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O vessel-making king! O vessel-making king! (1)</l>
<l>In the old town of vast area (4ab)</l>
<l>with a kiln that supports, in the wide dark sky, (3)</l>
<l>a big [colon of] smoke, brilliance accumulated like darkness become firm, (2)</l>
<l>O vessel-making king! (4cd)</l>
<l>Pitiable are you. What will become of you? (5)</l>
<l>Vaḷavan on a tall horse, with banners swaying on [his] elephants, (10)</l>
<l>descendant of the Cempiyar of far-shining excellence (9)</l>
<l>that is like the wide-rayed sun climbing the sky, (8)</l>
<l>of unlying fame that is praised by poets, (7)</l>
<l>with a lengthy long army which was laid out up to the limits of the ground, (6)</l>
<l>because he [now] has reached the world of the gods, (11)</l>
<l>if you need to form (13a-c)</l>
<l>an urn wide [enough] in area to cover such a one, (12)</l>
<l>is it at all possible for you to form from clay (13d+15)</l>
<l>the big mountain with the large earth as the wheel? (14)</l>
</lg>
